ocMA.OdeW4C1H.text = "Avvakoum 3:1-3. The notes in La Bible d’Alexandrie, XXIII: 4-9, are particularly valuable on these verses. Because Theman is in the south, for the Fathers it signifies Bethlehem, south of Jerusalem, the place where Christ was born. The words ‘shaded’ and ‘wooded’ are both ‘translations’ of the Hebrew name Paran, which was linked by the translator with a rare Hebrew word meaning ‘bough’."

