ocMA.OdeW7C11.text = "John 18:22. The word only occurs four times in the Bible, here and in the plural at Mark 14:65, John 19:3 and Isaias 50:6, ‘I gave my back to scourges and my cheeks to blows’.

The word alastor is used frequently of the devil in the liturgical texts, but it only occurs four times in the Septuagint, three of them in 4 Maccabees and one in 2 Maccabees, where it is used of Antiochus Epiphanes and once of the ‘avenger’ who will punish him. In classical Greek it seems to have originally meant an ‘avenging deity’."

